@Kevin P.


    I agree that the drop is dramatic, especially for countries like Mexico that started out with very high birthrates. I also think your question about the economy is an important one. The cost of living, housing, childcare, and even job stability can definitely influence how many kids people feel they can support. I made this point in my observation as well. 
    It is jarring to see how quickly the average has fallen, but it doesn’t mean people don’t want children it can just mean it's harder to afford a good life for them. The population isn’t necessarily shrinking everywhere YET, but the trend does make me question how the future will be.

